      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Cycling Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PELOTON is a bingo candidate:</span> At exactly 7 letters, PELOTON earns the 50-point bonus when you use all tiles. Hold P, E, L, O, T, O, N for a 59-point play. All common letters too.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CADENCE doubles the C:</span> Using two C tiles (3pts each) in one word clears premium consonants from your rack. CADENCE scores 11 points and leaves you with flexible vowel-heavy draws.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SPRINT hooks to SPRINTS:</span> Adding an S to SPRINT creates a 9-point play from an already-placed word. Look for front hooks too — SPRINTER (10pts) extends further.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
